<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4442&amp;p=18625#p18625"><![CDATA[
I'm sentimental.  I renamed the &quot;This PC&quot; to &quot;My Computer&quot;  If you right click on the desktop and choose personalize on the left is the &quot;Change Desktop Icons&quot;  I checke each one and then I chaned the &quot;This PC&quot; one to a more familiar icon.<br /><br />Yes, Disk management works very well.  I have also used Partition Commander and Paragon Partition Commander to change things around.  XP was not that good at drive partitions but there is sofware out there that made up for that shortcoming.<br /><br />I think I would need to install a program to run the same program, even though it resides on the XP partition.  It is not registered in the registry, nor has the Digital Link Libraries that Windows 8.1 would need to effective run any particular program.    I just was unsure if I could designate the same folder for the storage that I had with XP.  I mean, in Windows 8.1 there are psuedo folders that don't work that are merely place holders to file names to make old 32 bit software work right.  If I am understanding on this.  Most of the &quot;MY&quot; folders like pictures, documents, etc reside in a &quot;user&quot; folder now if I am correct.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9880">AKsarben</a> — Sat Apr 04, 2015 6:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
