<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4442&amp;p=18624#p18624"><![CDATA[
You will absolutely have access to any files stored on another drive... hell theres nothing stopping you from opening the old xp partition inside windows 8.1 to run a program off of it, or copy the settings from one of the programs installed... (you may need to assign a drive letter, though it should work automatically) right click on &quot;This Pc&quot;  icon once you get windows 8.1 installed select manage, then disk management. that will show all drives and partitions attached to your computer. From there you can add a drive letter to any partition or disk that isnt otherwise visible<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Sat Apr 04, 2015 3:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
